Read the readme file in sortgpt_toolkit folder inside sort-llm and run the following grid of training runs using the code and instruction in sortgpt_toolkit:
0.01 initialization scale for both layers
0.03 learning rate
k in [16, 32]
embedding size chosen from [64]
N (vocab size) chosen from [128, 256, 512, 1024]
Use seed 1 
run sequentially where each GPU only has one model running at a time and when one model is done we move to the next model
and we have all 8 GPUs running at once.
save the resulting checkpoints in new-grid folder in /mnt/task_runtime (in separate subfodlers there). save the checkpoints every 5000 number of iterations.
after each gpu finished its training run, start plotting the same plots as in plots_V64_B32_LR1e-02_MI10000_E64_H1_L2_ckpt10000 for the last checkpoint of the config you were training on that gpu, suing the same gpu.
